# Performance Rules

## Public Pages — Server Components First

```tsx
// ✅ Public page — no client JS needed
// app/(public)/projects/page.tsx
export default async function ProjectsPage() {
  const projects = await apiClient.get(API.PROJECTS.LIST);
  return <ProjectsGrid projects={projects} />;
}

// ❌ Wrong — adds unnecessary client bundle
"use client";
export default function ProjectsPage() {
  const { data } = useQuery(...); // Not needed for public read pages
}
```

Rule: **Never** use `useQuery` or `useEffect` for data on public `(public)/` pages — use RSC.

## Admin Pages — TanStack Query

Admin pages ARE client-interactive (CRUD, real-time updates) — `useQuery` is correct here.  
But always server-paginate:

```ts
// ✅ Server pagination — never fetch all records
useLeads({ page: 1, limit: 20 });
useAdminProjects({ page, limit: 20, sector: filter });

// ❌ Never
useLeads({ limit: 9999 }); // Don't pull entire table
```

## Images

```tsx
// ✅ Always next/image
import Image from "next/image";
<Image src={url} alt="..." width={400} height={300} />
// or with fill:
<Image src={url} alt="..." fill className="object-cover" />

// ❌ Never raw <img>
<img src={url} alt="..." />
```

## Zustand — No Server Data

```ts
// ✅ Zustand for UI state
useModalStore()      // isOpen, selectedId
useAdminFiltersStore() // filterStatus, searchTerm

// ❌ Never put API response data in Zustand
// TanStack Query is the cache for server state
```

## Bundle Discipline

- No new npm packages without checking if existing library covers it
- framer-motion, sonner, lucide-react — already installed, use them
- Never re-install what's already in `package.json`
- `"use client"` boundary as deep as possible — minimize client JS on public pages
